        <body>
            <div type="edition">
                <div type="textpart" subtype="chapter">
                    <ab><title>Numbers 8</title>
                        <milestone unit="line" n="9" />
                        <l><emph>Parashat Behaalotecha</emph></l>
                        <milestone unit="line" n="10" />
                        <l n="1">And the Lord spoke
                            <milestone unit="line" n="11" />
                             to Moses, saying,</l>
                        <l n="2">‘Speak
                            <milestone unit="line" n="12" />
                             to Aaron, and say to him, “When you light the candles,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="13" />
                             the seven lamps shall give light opposite the front of the
                            lampstand.”’</l>
                        <milestone unit="line" n="14" />
                        <l n="3">And Aaron did so. He lighted its candles opposite the front of
                            <milestone unit="line" n="15" />
                             lampstand, as the Lord commanded
                            <milestone unit="line" n="16" />
                             Moses.</l>
                        <l n="4">And this is the work of the lampstand: hammered work
                            <milestone unit="line" n="17" />
                             of gold, including its shaft, including its leaves, it was hammered
                            work.
                            <milestone unit="line" n="18" />
                             According to the appearance that the Lord had shown Moses, so he made
                            the
                            <milestone unit="line" n="19" />
                             lampstand.</l>
                        <l n="5">And the Lord spoke to Moses, saying,
                            <milestone unit="page" n="225r" />
                            <milestone unit="line" n="1" />
                             ‘Take the Levites from among
                            <milestone unit="line" n="2" />
                             the children of Israel and make them pure.</l>
                        <l n="7">And
                            <milestone unit="line" n="3" />
                             thus shall you do to them, to make them pure: Sprinkle
                            <milestone unit="line" n="4" />
                             purifying water on them, and they shall pass a razor over all
                            <milestone unit="line" n="5" />
                             their body, and they shall wash their clothes and make themselves
                            clean.</l>
                        <milestone unit="line" n="6" />
                        <l n="8">Then they shall take a calf, the young of cattle and
                            <milestone unit="line" n="7" />
                             its grain offering, fine flour mixed with oil, and you shall take a
                            second calf, the young
                            <milestone unit="line" n="8" />
                             of cattle, for a sin offering.</l>
                        <l n="9">And you shall bring forward
                            <milestone unit="line" n="9" />
                             the Levites before the tent of meeting, and you shall assemble
                            <milestone unit="line" n="10" />
                             the whole congregation of the children of Israel.</l>
                        <l n="10">And
                            <milestone unit="line" n="11" />
                             you shall bring the Levites before the Lord: and
                            <milestone unit="line" n="12" />
                             the children of Israel shall reach out their hands over the
                            Levites.</l>
                        <milestone unit="line" n="13" />
                        <l n="11">And Aaron shall elevate the Levites
                            <milestone unit="line" n="14" />
                             before the Lord for a wave offering from the children of Israel, and
                            they shall be
                            <milestone unit="line" n="15" />
                             to serve the service of the Lord.</l>
                        <l n="12">And
                            <milestone unit="line" n="16" />
                             the Levites shall reach out their hands over the heads
                            <milestone unit="line" n="17" />
                             of the calves. And make one a sin offering and
                            <milestone unit="line" n="18" />
                             one a burnt offering to the Lord, to ask for atonement for the
                            Levites.</l>
                        <milestone unit="line" n="19" />
                        <l n="13">And you shall stand the Levites
                            <milestone unit="line" n="20" />
                             before Aaron and before his sons, and you shall elevate them
                            <milestone unit="line" n="21" />
                             for a wave offering to the Lord.</l>
                        <l n="14">And you shall separate the Levites
                            <milestone unit="page" n="225v" />
                            <milestone unit="line" n="1" />
                             from among the children of Israel, and the Levites shall be mine.</l>
                        <milestone unit="line" n="2" />
                        <l n="15">And after that the Levites shall come to do the service
                            <milestone unit="line" n="3" />
                             in the tent of meeting: if you have made them pure and elevated
                            <milestone unit="line" n="4" />
                             them for a wave offering.</l>
                        <l n="16">Because they are given, given,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="5" />
                             to me from among the children of Israel: In place of all opening
                            <milestone unit="line" n="6" />
                             of a womb, the firstborn of all the children of Israel,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="7" />
                             I have taken them to me.</l>
                        <l n="17">Because all the firstborn
                            <milestone unit="line" n="8" />
                             of the children of Israel are mine, both man and animal. On the day
                            that I struck
                            <milestone unit="line" n="9" />
                             every firstborn in the land of Egypt I sanctified them for myself.</l>
                        <milestone unit="line" n="10" />
                        <l n="18">And I have taken the Levites in place of all the firstborn
                            <milestone unit="line" n="11" />
                             among the children of Israel.</l>
                        <l n="19">And I have given the
                            <milestone unit="line" n="12" />
                             Levites — they are given — to Aaron and to his sons
                            <milestone unit="line" n="13" />
                             from among the children of Israel, to serve the service
                            <milestone unit="line" n="14" />
                             of the children of Israel in the tent of meeting, and to ask for
                            atonement
                            <milestone unit="line" n="15" />
                             for the children of Israel, so there will not be, among the children of
                            Israel,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="16" />
                             plague when the children of Israel come near to the Holy.’</l>
                        <milestone unit="line" n="17" />
                        <l n="20">And Moses and Aaron and all the congregation of the children
                            <milestone unit="line" n="18" />
                             of Israel did to the Levites as the Lord commanded Moses concerning the
                            Levites;
                            <milestone unit="line" n="19" />
                             the children of Israel did so to them.</l>
                        <l n="21">
                            <milestone unit="line" n="20" />
                             And the Levites were purified, and they washed their clothes,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="21" />
                             and Aaron elevated them as a wave offering before the Lord,
                            <milestone unit="page" n="226r" />
                            <milestone unit="line" n="1" />
                             and Aaron asked for atonement for them to purify them.</l>
                        <milestone unit="line" n="2" />
                        <l n="22">And after that, <addSpan spanTo="#Num-008-add001_trl"
                                 /><emph>so</emph><anchor type="addSpan" xml:id="Num-008-add001_trl"
                             /> came the Levites to serve
                            <milestone unit="line" n="3" />
                             their service in the tent of meeting before Aaron
                            <milestone unit="line" n="4" />
                             and before his sons as the Lord had commanded
                            <milestone unit="line" n="5" />
                             Moses concerning the Levites; they did so to them.</l>
                        <milestone unit="line" n="6" />
                        <l n="23">And the Lord spoke to Moses, saying,</l>
                        <milestone unit="line" n="7" />
                        <l n="24">‘This is what you shall do to the Levites: from twenty-five
                            <milestone unit="line" n="8" />
                             years old and upward they shall join up to do military service by the
                            tent
                            <milestone unit="line" n="9" />
                             of meeting.</l>
                        <l n="25">And from the age of fifty years they shall return from the
                            military
                            <milestone unit="line" n="10" />
                             service, and shall serve no more.</l>
                        <l n="26">
                            <milestone unit="line" n="11" />
                             And he shall minister with their brothers in the tent of meeting, to
                            keep
                            <milestone unit="line" n="12" />
                             the charge, and he shall do no service. Thus shall you do to the
                            Levites
                            <milestone unit="line" xml:id="Num008-P226r-L13_trl" n="13"
                                next="ADub.III.73.004.009.trl.xml#Num009-P226r-L13_trl" />
                             regarding their charge.’ </l>
                    </ab>
